.TH "drm_dsc_pps_payload_pack" 9 "drm_dsc_pps_payload_pack" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dsc_pps_payload_pack \- Populates the DSC PPS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_dsc_pps_payload_pack
.BI "(struct drm_dsc_picture_parameter_set *pps_payload "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_dsc_config *dsc_cfg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pps_payload" 12
Bitwise struct for DSC Picture Parameter Set. This is defined
by \fIstruct drm_dsc_picture_parameter_set\fP
.IP "dsc_cfg" 12
DSC Configuration data filled by driver as defined by
\fIstruct drm_dsc_config\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
DSC source device sends a picture parameter set (PPS) containing the
information required by the sink to decode the compressed frame. Driver
populates the DSC PPS struct using the DSC configuration parameters in
the order expected by the DSC Display Sink device. For the DSC, the sink
device expects the PPS payload in big endian format for fields
that span more than 1 byte.
